The presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Atiku Abubakar, has arrived Sani Abacha Stadium in Kano, venue of his rally. Atiku was accompanied by his running mate, Peter Obi, Senator Rabi’u Musa Kwankwaso, the National Chairman of PDP, Uche Secondus, Atiku’s campaign director, Otunba Gbenga Daniel and Senate President Abubakar Bukola Saraki. Atiku and his entourage arrived the stadium at exactly 5:50pm. The former vice president was received by mammoth crowd of PDP supporters. Atiku and his entourage could not come down from the luxurious vehicle that brought them into the stadium due to throng of party supporters and well-wishers in the area. PDP supporters paint Kano red as they await Atiku's arrival Atiku lands at Kano International Airport, sets for rally Atiku's wife arrives Kano for husband's rally